PATCH: Add new migration for shop settings seeding
This commit introduces a new migration file for seeding the 'shop_settings' table in the shop connection. The seeding process, on this particular migration up, inserts an entry with 'enabled' being set 'OFF'.

FIX: Rename migration files and add timestamps to shop settings
Migration files have been renamed to reflect changes in their execution order. A timestamp field was also added to the 'shop_settings' table, with 'created_at' and 'updated_at' fields being auto-populated on insert. This change should enhance data tracking and organization.

FIX: Rename migration files and add timestamps to shop settings
Migration files have been renamed to reflect changes in their execution order. A timestamp field was also added to the 'shop_settings' table, with 'created_at' and 'updated_at' fields being auto-populated on insert. This change should enhance data tracking and organization.

PATCH: Update database connection configurations
The configuration of database connections was updated across multiple models and migrations for better segmentation and management. Some models are set to use the newly introduced 'shop', 'akce' and 'blog' database connections instead of the default. In the database.php configuration file, SQLite and PostgreSQL connection settings were removed and new 'shop', 'akce', and 'blog' MySQL connections were added.

PATCH: Add: Command to send schedule emails and redesigned email templates
The SendSchedulesEmail command has been added to automate the process of sending schedule emails to users, specifically those with an "platform.systems.events" access. A new email template, 'users/invoice.blade.php', has been created to inform users about their upcoming schedules. A significant change to the '@events' field has also been made in the 'admins/schedules.blade.php' email template, adding a more standardized time display.
